<dl id="n01019c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n01" href="#n01019c">N01 (VI.B.10)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n01all.htm#n01019c"> 19(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Allmers = Renan</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[the entire story, as recapped by Monahan]</font> <small> Michael Monahan, <a name="MMAL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MMAL"><cite title="source">Adventures in Life and Letters</cite></a> (1912) 338-351 [Henriette <mark>Renan</mark>]</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Joyce notes the parallel between Alfred Allmers, the deluded protagonist of Ibsen&apos;s <cite>Eyolf</cite> (1894), who lives with his wife and half-sister, that suffer for his ideals, and Renan, who also lived with his wife and sister, Henriette. Cf. also VI.A.0301 (&lsquo;Exiles&rsquo; II): &lsquo;Henriette (cf Trist-Renan)&rsquo;, and David Hayman, <cite>The Wake in Transit</cite>, 181n.  <br>Raphael transcription: <a name="c05104b" href="c05all.htm#c05104b">VI.C.05:104(b)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
